danish: Vi cykler en tur. I weekenden cyklede vi en tur.
english: We're going on a bike tour (lit. biking a tour). On the weekend, we went on a bike tour (lit. biked a tour).

danish: Vi glæder os til at se jer!
english: We look forward to seeing you!

danish: Vi går til venstre ned ad Amagerbrogade.

english: We're fine. (lit. We have it good.)

danish: Vi havde det hyggeligt i Odense.
english: We had a nice time in Odense.

danish: Vi kan godt lide vores nye hjem.
Vi kørte til Århus i mandags.
english: We drove to Århus on Monday.
We'll have to take out our umbrellas!
We'll see each other at half seven (lit. half eight).

danish: Vi ses klokken kvart over ni.
english: We'll see each other at quarter past nine.

danish: Vi skal bo på et dejligt værelse.
english: We will stay (lit. live) in a nice room.
We have to find a place to park.

danish: Vi skal flyve til Rom i weekenden.
english: We will fly to Rome on the weekend.

danish: Vi skal køre i bil til Esbjerg.
english: We will drive by car to Esbjerg.
We will make a fool's letter.

danish: Vi skal med en færge kl 17.54.
english: We will (go) with a ferry at 17:54.

danish: Vi skal planlægge vores ferie i næste uge.
english: We will plan our vacation next week.

danish: Vi skal på udflugt med familien.
english: We will (go) on an excursion with the family.
We have to get off soon!

danish: Vi skyder nytåret ind med fyrværkeri.
english: We see in the New Year with fireworks.

danish: Vi tager bilen og kører 543 kilometer på en dag.
english: We're taking the car and driving 543 kilometers in a day.

danish: Vi tilmeldte os med det samme.
Vi vil gerne blive i cirka to uger.
english: We would like to stay about two weeks.
Would you like a receipt (lit. with)?

danish: Vil du have noget at spise?
english: Would you like something to eat?

danish: Vil du med mig til koncerten?
english: Are you coming to the concert with me?

danish: Vil du med til en fest på fredag?
english: Would you like to come (lit. with) to a party on Friday?

danish: Vores seng er blød og varm.
english: Our bed is soft and warm.
Here you go, here are your tickets.

danish: at gå i seng med én
english: to sleep (lit. to go into bed) with someone
to pass on greetings from someone
to drive - drove, to ride - rode
to knock the cat out of the barrel

danish: at være af en anden mening
english: to be of a different opinion
a grandmother (lit. fathermother), a grandfather (lit. fatherfather)
a grandmother (lit. mothermother), a grandfather (lit. motherfather)

danish: Æblet er modent, det er helt rødt. (et æble)
english: The apple is ripe, it's completely red.

danish: Æggene skal koge i syv minutter.(et æg)
english: The eggs need to cook for seven minutes.
